From: Octopus Orchestrator upstream PR draft wave (M0-17)
Subject: [PATCH] gateway: accept capsOcto on role: node connect

Let a node advertise Octopus Orchestrator host capabilities during the
Gateway connect handshake. Adds a new optional capsOcto field to
ConnectParamsSchema (version, adapters list, maxArms) and stores it on
the NodeSession so scheduler code can filter octo-eligible nodes via
the existing NodeRegistry.listConnected() / get() query surface.

Purely additive: no existing key changes shape. Nodes that omit the
field are unaffected. Gateways with octo.enabled: false accept and
store the field anyway — nodes connect to multiple heads and the wire
protocol must be forward-compatible per head. Dispatch and scheduler
placement remain out of scope for this PR.

Draft authored against upstream commit 9ece252.

